EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to state financial administration; authorizing the
Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau to enter into
any contracts necessary to assist the Economic Forum and
the Technical Advisory Committee on Future State
Revenues in carrying out their duties; revising the date by
which certain reports of the Economic Forum are required
to be prepared and presented; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, the Governor is required, on or before July 1 of each even-
2 numbered year, to impanel an Economic Forum, which consists of persons who
3 have the expertise necessary for economic forecasting and are appointed by the
4 Governor. (NRS 353.226) Existing law requires the Economic Forum to make
5 projections for economic indicators and provide an accurate estimate of the revenue
6 that will be collected by the State for general, unrestricted uses during the next
7 biennium and report such projections and estimates to the Governor and the
8 Legislature. (NRS 353.228) Existing law also requires that all projections of
9 revenue and any other information concerning future state revenue contained in the
10 biennial budget proposed to the Legislature be based upon the projections and
11 estimates prepared by the Economic Forum. (NRS 353.230, 353.246) Existing law
12 creates the Technical Advisory Committee on Future State Revenues and requires it
13 to provide all assistance requested by the Economic Forum. (NRS 353.229) Under
14 existing law, the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau and the Chief of the
15 Budget Division of the Office of Finance are required to jointly provide the
16 Economic Forum and the Technical Advisory Committee with meeting rooms,
17 staff, data processing services and clerical assistance. (NRS 353.227) Sections 1
18 and 3 of this bill: (1) remove data processing services from the list of jointly
19 provided items; and (2) authorize the Director to enter into any contracts necessary
20 to assist the Economic Forum and the Technical Advisory Committee in carrying
-
