21 out their duties, including contracts for revenue forecasting and data processing
22 services.
23 Existing law requires the Economic Forum, on or before December 3 of each
24 even-numbered year, to prepare a written report of its projections of economic
25 indicators and estimate of future state revenue and present the report to the
26 Governor and the Legislature. Additionally, existing law requires the Economic
27 Forum, on or before May 1 of each odd-numbered year, to prepare a written report
28 confirming or revising those projections and that estimate and present that report to
29 the Governor and the Legislature. (NRS 353.228) Section 2 of this bill moves the
30 date by which the latter report is required to be prepared and presented from May 1
31 of each odd-numbered year to April 1 of each odd-numbered year.
